<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="56" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1463,1886]" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1463,1489]" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
1) body reddish-brown, except head black, fore and middle legs orange, and hind leg reddish (coxa reddish-brown); 2) fore wing fuscous, veins at proximal half black and apical half light brown, pterostigma yellow; 3) head, in dorsal view, with gena slightly concave behind eyes; 4) face smooth and without a carina; 5) occipital carina upcurved and not reduced dorsally; 6) pronotum with the pocket-like structure not reduced longitudinally; 7) epicnemial carina absent; 8) sternite I with a rounded swelling posteriorly; 9) female with tarsal claw with more or less square lobe, and with apex overtaking the lobe (tarsal claw single in males); 10) female with ovipositor sheath about 1.0 × as long as the hind tibia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="56" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1463,1886]" box="[199,1238,1715,1741]" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1715,1741]" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,431,1715,1741]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">Brazil</collectingCountry>
